FBIS3-56335 "drsov010_a_94081" FBIS-SOV-94-010 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Jan 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Nuclear Reactor Purchase Discussed TA1401110494 Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ in Hebrew 14 Jan 94 p C3 TA1401110494 Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ Language: Hebrew Article Type:BFN [Report by 'Amos Be'er] [Excerpt] "The Russians are interested in selling Israel nuclear reactors for electricity production." This was reported by Energy Minister Moshe Shahal, currently visiting the CIS republics. According to Shahal, the implementation of the deal depends on Israel's ability to purchase the Russian reactors in view of the technical, political, and economic constraints. The minister explained that the Russians are willing to sell five [as published] energy products to Israel, in addition to nuclear energy: crude oil, natural gas, petroleum distillates (such as benzine), and know-how for the production of alternative energy. [passage omitted]
